# Groth16 keys are server-generated together by setup_live_zk.sh (like
# node_modules) so the proving key (.zkey) and verifying key (_vkey.json) always
# come from the SAME trusted setup and match. They survive deploys as untracked
# files; run setup_live_zk.sh once after a fresh checkout to make circuits live.
*.zkey
*.wtns
*_0000.zkey
*_0001.zkey
# trusted-setup ceremony files (downloaded on the server)
*.ptau
*_vkey.json
# local build tooling (downloaded circom binary + Windows-safe snarkjs API helpers)
bin/
_setup_local.cjs
_verify_local.cjs
_zkcount.cjs
_zkdiag.cjs
# transient harness / build artifacts (zk_roundtrip_harness.sh, build_new_circuit.sh, served_prove)
.harness_tmp/
.harness*.log
.neg_test.log
.build_*.log
.ptau*.log
build_new/
node_modules
